Reading the Data

Spark Session Spark_Session_Configuration is needed for the data frame creation

- Read
- processes
- Write

Write read code :

First we need to config Spark Config and do the
[SPARK_APP_CONFIGS]
- spark.app.name = Hello Spark
- spark.master = local[3]

this is the property file where spark env config will be configured
lib.utils class i am creating spark config for get_spark_app_config
import configparser
from pyspark import SparkConfig()

def get_spark_app_config():
	spark_conf = SparkConfig()
	config = config.ConfigParser().read("spark.conf")

	for key,value in config.items("SPARK_APP_CONFIGS"): 
		spark_conf.set(key,value)

	return spark_conf

Configuring the sparkconf for further use in read

import sys
import os 

from pyspark import SparkConf
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from lib.logger import Log4J
from lib.utils import get_spark_app_config

if __name__ == "__main__":
	conf = get_spark_app_config()
	spark = SparkSession.builder \
			.config(conf=conf) \
			.getOrCreate()
	logger = Log4J(spark)
	if len(sys.argy) != 2:
		logger.error("Usage: HelloSpark <filename>")
		sys.exit(-1)

	logger.info("Starting Spark Session")

	conf_out = spark.SparkContext.getConf()
	logger.info("Finished HelloSpark") 

	# ---- Read The Dataframe ----
	spark_df = spark.read \
				.option('header','true') \
				.csv(sys.argv[1])
	spark.stop()

Here we are reading a csv file and this is complex and flexible
till here we are reading the data dataframe and with header is true as we have first rows in csv file is header

now we need to check for DataFrame DataType

Datatype

So for defining data frame data type we need to use inferSchema


spark_df = spark.read \
			.option('header','true') \
			.option('inferSchema', 'true') \
			.csv (sys.argv[1])

Here it will do intelligent guess for datatype and put a suitable datatype.
to view the dataframe we need to use

spark_df.show()

 
![[ED-202406171359.excalidraw|1000]]


After this Spark Session will start the executors
as we configured the CPU, Memory, Executors are
Configured to the spark session.

work as Driver allocation and as well providing resources like
- Cluster manager
- Resource Manager
- Container Manager

Here Spark will try to minimize the network bandwidth for loading data from HDFS to the JVM Memory.

This is Spark internal Optimizer while assigning the partition to these executor

Spark will Try its best -- Spark and Cluster Manager work together
achieve the best possible localization.
